We stand with all front line defenders who have been holding it down for the past 9 months.⁠
⁠
We stand to end colonial violence and un-checked resource extraction within our last critical endangered ecosystems. ⁠
⁠
We stand against the RCMP's establishment of unlawful exclusion zones and against the tactics employed by the RCMP, BC NDP, and BC FORESTRY.⁠
⁠
We reject BC NDP, John Horgan's and BC Forestry's campaign of misinformation.⁠
⁠

node.text: It’s not Loggers vs Environmentalists - we all want the thing. node.text:
NO MORE FUNDING FOR THE RCMP TO ABUSE PEACEFUL PROTESTERS AT FAIRY CREEK. Repost from @fairycreekblockade
•
DAILY UPDATE 📌 (Sept 2nd) THE PEOPLE SAY NO TO RCMP SPENDING INCREASE - LEG LAWN HUNGER STRIKE CONTINUES

843 arrests to date (4 Today)

“This is how we "fight." Peaceful protest. Non-violent. Together as One. Recreating the magic of Fairy Creek in the middle of an intersection in Vancouver! We are always on Creator Time ” - Rainbow Eyes

▪️When the RCMP has the audacity to demand a larger budget for enforcement at Fairy Creek, we will be the first to stand up and say “enough is enough.” A demonstration was held on the Cambie Street Bridge in Vancouver on Thursday in opposition to this absurd request. The obvious answer is to reject this atrocious use of tax dollars. 

▪️There is no room for the government to pour more funding into an institution brutalizing peaceful protestors, acting outside of the law, actively ensuring we don’t meet our provincial climate commitments, doubling down on fear and perpetuation rather than truth and reconciliation, and unjustly targeting BIPOC defenders time and time again. There’s also no room for protecting large corporate entities in the for-profit extraction of irreplaceable ancient forests, especially those that are such potent carbon sinks and contain so many endangered species, ESPECIALLY during a global climate and ecological crisis. It is long past time that these issues start being taken seriously.

▪️Two people were extracted from "French Trench" today, and two from the next one over known as "Christmas Tree.” RCMP moved the frontline back twice as “green guys” worked to dismantle "Beaver Dam" further up the hill. When pressure for a 3rd line shift was exerted, land defenders collectively refused to budge and the line held solid where it was at Christmas Tree. 

▪️In other news, forest defender Lalita is now on the 17th day of his hunger strike for ancient forests out on the Victoria legislature lawn. Please visit to help him keep his resolve firm in his goal to #fast4fairycreek for 40 days or more. 

COME TO CAMP!
@dailyhivevancouver @cbcvancouver @viawesome @lifewithleeta @schandraherbert
